### Static
--> Static keyword is used to define class-level memebr, static variable, and methods belong to class not to any individiual object.
--> this means they can acess without creating an Object

## fundamental Concept of Static
 --> Static Variable
 --> Static Block
 --> Static Methods

 ** Static Variable:- 
  --> whose value persists through entire Program excution.
  --> it's allocated memory once and remain in memory until the program ends

  ** Static Block
  --> Excuted Once , when the class is first loaded into memory, it is used to initalize static variable or perform one setup task

  ** Static methods
  --> Excute only once when class is loaded

  ** Default value of Static variable is 
       int -> 0;
       double -> 0.0
       String -> null;
       boolean -> false;

** Code
    class Program
    {
       Static int a;
       Static int b;
       int p;
       int q;
       static {
          System.out.println("Inside static block");
          a = 10;
          b = 20;
          }
           {
              System.out.println("Inside non-static block");
              p = 100;
              q = 200;
           }

           Static disp1(){
           System.out.println("Inside static method ");
           System.out.println(a);
           System.out.println(b);
           }
            Static disp2(){
           System.out.println("Inside non-static method ");
           System.out.println(p);
           System.out.println(q);
           }
    }
            public Static void main(String[] args) {
            Program p1 = new Program();
            p1.disp1();
            p2.disp();
            }



       ### SHORT  Dry-Run of this code   
 -->   Class load hoti hai → static variables a=0, b=0 create hote hain
- Static block run (once) → output: Inside static block, values: a=10, b=20
- main() start hota hai
- Object create (new Program())
- instance vars: p=0, q=0
- non-static block run → output: Inside non-static block, values: p=100, q=200
- Static method disp1() call → prints 10, 20
- Non-static method disp2() call → prints 100, 200

O/P   --> Inside static block
          Inside non-static block
          Inside static method
          10
           20
        Inside non-static method
        100
        200

